                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE LEE</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18540918-989-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18540918-989-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18540918-989-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for a like offence.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540918-name-83" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-83" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-83" type="surname" value="THORPE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-83" type="given" value="WILLIAM BECK"></interp>WILLIAM BECK THORPE</persName>
                  </hi>. I carry on business as a butcher, in Newgate Market. On 2nd Sept., the prisoner came to my stand, about twenty minutes before 9 o'clock—he bought a small shoulder of mutton, which came to 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me in payment a crown piece—I said, "This is a bad one; how came you by this?"—he would not give me any answer—I asked him where he lived—he would not tell me—I asked who his employer was—he would not tell me—I gave him into custody, and gave the crown to the beadle.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540918-name-84" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-84" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-84" type="surname" value="KENTISH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-84" type="given" value="JOHN BENJAMIN"></interp>JOHN BENJAMIN KENTISH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am beadle of Newgate Market. I received the prisoner from the last witness—he gave me this crown—I asked the prisoner for his address—he refused to give me any—he said, "I am not bound to give any account of myself to you"—I conveyed him to the station,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185409180025"></xptr>
               <p>and he refused to give any account to the inspector—I found on him a half crown, and some other money, which was good.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540918-name-85" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-85" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-85" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-85" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint. This crown is bad.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I changed a half sovereign in Greek-street, Soho; I do not know the name of the landlord; I have been in the habit of being invited to dine with a young couple on Sundays; I went to buy this shoulder of mutton for them, when I was taken; I was not aware that it was bad.</p>
